
[1]bespeaak

   BESPEA'AK, v.t. pret. bespoke; pp. bespoke, bespoken. [be and speak.]

   1. To speak for beforehand; to order or engage against a future time;
   as, to bespeak a seat in a public coach.

   My lade is bespoke.

   2. To forebode; to foretell.

   They started fears, and bespoke dangers, to scare the allies.

   3. To speak to; to address. This sense is mostly poetical.

   He thus the queen bespoke.

   4. To betoken; to show; to indicate by external marks or appearances;
   as, his manners bespeak him a gentleman.
